metrics_conclusion: In terms of chords and melody, Spectrum is more complex than the typical song, having above average scores in Chord Complexity, Melodic Complexity, Chord Progression Novelty and Chord-Bass Melody.
key_conclusion:
Spectrum is written in the key of C Minor.  

According to the Theorytab database, it is the 3rd most popular key among Minor keys and     the 9th most popular  among all keys. Minor keys, along with major keys, are a common choice for popular music.  The three most important chords, built off the 1st, 4th and 5th scale degrees are all minor chords (C minor, F minor, and G minor).

See the C Minor Cheat Sheet for popular chords, chord progressions, downloadable midi files and more!

metadata.editComments: Changed the Cadd9 chords back to I(add9). @Vaz123 Yes, I'm sure. At first glance, they can look like secondary dominant chords. However, if you listen and look at the balance of the phrase, these chords function stronger as mode mixture chords. Zedd does this kind of thing in some of his other tracks, so it is more likely to be the case.
